WEBVTT

01:19.726 --> 01:22.044
Out of the darkness

01:23.125 --> 01:25.053
Something is waiting.

01:27.513 --> 01:31.828
Something you must overcome

01:33.403 --> 01:38.398
No time for weakness or hesitating

01:41.968 --> 01:45.745
This time it's got to be done

01:47.867 --> 01:49.804
Tales of power

01:50.956 --> 01:53.333
Tales of power

01:54.650 --> 01:58.206
Tales of power all around you

01:58.410 --> 02:01.048
Into the void you've been hurled

02:01.042 --> 02:05.428
Tales of power will surround you

02:05.428 --> 02:10.103
Now is the hour for
you to stop the world

02:13.940 --> 02:17.505
- Sammy, how you doing?

02:17.961 --> 02:20.009
- Hey guy, where you been?

02:20.517 --> 02:21.816
Say, why don't you wait outside and we'll

02:21.818 --> 02:23.226
go out for a couple of beers?

02:23.224 --> 02:24.902
- I can't, Sam, I gotta pick up Walter.

02:24.896 --> 02:26.754
- How is my godson?

02:26.761 --> 02:30.188
- Walter's great, Walter is always great.

02:37.289 --> 02:38.507
Are you ready for this?

02:38.503 --> 02:39.493
- Yeah.

02:41.543 --> 02:42.821
- Are you holding on?

02:42.819 --> 02:44.367
- Yeah, are you holding on?

02:44.375 --> 02:45.633
- I got you, Walter.

02:45.631 --> 02:47.459
I'm right here.

02:48.349 --> 02:49.788
Keep peddling.

02:49.788 --> 02:51.405
Keep peddling.

02:51.854 --> 02:54.202
Okay, Walter, you're on your own.

02:54.199 --> 02:55.648
You got it?

02:55.701 --> 02:57.160
- Dad.

02:58.141 --> 02:59.690
Look, I'm doing it!

02:59.686 --> 03:01.554
- Attaboy, Walter, you got it.

03:01.550 --> 03:03.239
- I'm riding alone.

03:03.245 --> 03:05.972
- I know, I know!

03:08.317 --> 03:09.566
- Whoa!

03:16.601 --> 03:17.941
- Four.

03:18.539 --> 03:19.797
- Get serious.

03:19.799 --> 03:21.198
Five.

03:21.624 --> 03:23.403
Six.

03:32.107 --> 03:34.865
You guys, stop, stop, stop.

03:35.517 --> 03:36.945
I said stop, stop.

03:36.952 --> 03:38.480
I said stop.

03:39.589 --> 03:40.888
- He started it.

03:40.884 --> 03:43.152
- Stop it, I said break it up.

03:43.549 --> 03:45.626
Now what do I teach you guys?

03:45.892 --> 03:47.960
- To be nice to people.

03:47.959 --> 03:49.877
- Yes, and?

03:49.877 --> 03:53.204
- Not to use what you
teach us to hurt people.

03:54.291 --> 03:55.500
- Good.

03:55.923 --> 03:58.380
So do you guys want to
beat each others' face in

03:58.378 --> 04:01.354
or do you want to shake
hands and be friends?

04:01.351 --> 04:02.999
- Friends.

04:05.453 --> 04:08.280
- Okay, I want you to be
best of friends, understand?

04:08.308 --> 04:09.507
- Yes sir.

04:09.609 --> 04:11.088
- All right, let's continue.

04:11.090 --> 04:12.848
Left and reverse punch one.

04:19.466 --> 04:21.053
- Mr. Lee.

04:21.079 --> 04:23.438
Excuse me, I think you should see this.

04:23.443 --> 04:24.622
- Everybody.

04:24.625 --> 04:26.224
Elliot, take over.

04:40.936 --> 04:43.304
- Ma, I've been asked to try out for the

04:43.302 --> 04:45.690
US National Karate Team.

04:45.976 --> 04:46.845
- Can I see it?

04:46.850 --> 04:47.899
- Yeah.

04:52.445 --> 04:54.963
- Are you seriously considering this?

04:55.651 --> 04:57.899
Don't they know about your shoulder?

04:58.017 --> 04:59.816
- Ma, my shoulder's all right.

04:59.818 --> 05:02.835
- Yeah, if you call plastic
cartilage in a steel pin

05:02.833 --> 05:04.551
all right, it's all right.

05:05.398 --> 05:07.246
Your shoulder's junk.

05:08.241 --> 05:10.528
What happens if you get hurt again?

05:10.521 --> 05:12.279
You could be paralyzed or something.

05:12.279 --> 05:13.718
- Calm down.

05:15.485 --> 05:18.153
Mama, I got nothing here.

05:18.160 --> 05:19.599
Nothing.

05:20.570 --> 05:24.156
Competing was the only
thing that made me feel...

05:25.577 --> 05:27.355
You saw me.

05:28.614 --> 05:30.791
- Yeah, I saw you.

05:33.046 --> 05:34.954
- Dad, I'm in bed.

05:36.786 --> 05:39.214
- And Walter, he's only five years old.

05:39.216 --> 05:40.754
He needs his father at home.

05:40.750 --> 05:42.319
What about your son?

05:42.327 --> 05:44.416
- What about my son?

05:45.897 --> 05:50.132
Mama, I love you.

05:52.226 --> 05:55.173
Walter and I will work it out, okay?

05:57.170 --> 06:01.915
And they were both wounded,
but they would not stop.

06:01.944 --> 06:04.761
Lancelot and Arthur
battled for a full day,

06:04.757 --> 06:07.864
finally defeating the evil Mordred.

06:07.868 --> 06:10.735
And the kingdom rejoiced
as they rode through

06:10.734 --> 06:14.171
the land together again as two friends.

06:14.656 --> 06:16.554
Da da da!

06:16.729 --> 06:17.608
- Wow.

06:17.603 --> 06:19.042
- Wow.

06:21.066 --> 06:24.123
- So when would you go
away if you go away?

06:26.070 --> 06:27.878
- That's up to us.

06:28.354 --> 06:29.833
What do you think?

06:29.835 --> 06:30.765
- Can I come?

06:30.763 --> 06:32.510
- No, you've got school.

06:32.509 --> 06:35.086
- How long would you be gone for?

06:35.680 --> 06:39.097
- If I make the team,
maybe a couple of months.

06:39.095 --> 06:40.344
- Like two?

06:40.342 --> 06:42.309
- Or more like three.

06:42.388 --> 06:43.736
- What do you get if you win?

06:45.051 --> 06:46.050
- A medal.

06:46.053 --> 06:47.002
- Can I have it?

06:47.001 --> 06:47.650
- Yes.

06:47.651 --> 06:48.630
- Then you'd better win.

06:48.631 --> 06:49.820
- Okay, I will.

06:49.814 --> 06:50.643
- Promise?

06:50.645 --> 06:52.104
- I promise.

06:52.844 --> 06:55.111
So I guess it's all set then, huh?

06:55.107 --> 06:56.247
- Okay.

06:56.248 --> 06:57.197
- You sure?
- Yeah.

06:57.196 --> 06:58.234
- You positive?
- Mm-hmm.

06:58.241 --> 06:59.130
- Really, truly?
- Yes.

06:59.125 --> 07:00.194
- Absolutely?
- Yes.

07:00.191 --> 07:01.290
- Okay.

07:04.428 --> 07:05.957
Here you go.

07:08.073 --> 07:10.031
You have sweet dreams.

07:10.394 --> 07:11.922
- I love you, daddy.

07:11.926 --> 07:13.894
- I love you too, Walter.

07:14.174 --> 07:15.243
Night night.

07:15.240 --> 07:16.578
- Goodnight.

07:19.606 --> 07:20.455
Dad?

07:20.458 --> 07:21.697
- Hmm?

07:21.694 --> 07:23.502
- You better win.

07:24.145 --> 07:25.673
- You got it.

07:48.057 --> 07:49.926
- Kim Yung.

07:55.419 --> 07:56.248
Cho Han.

08:00.748 --> 08:01.697
Tung Sun.

08:05.549 --> 08:07.248
Kwon Sae Jin.

08:23.938 --> 08:26.146
- Korea! Korea!

08:46.524 --> 08:48.432
- Goddamn circus.

09:00.459 --> 09:02.177
- Mind if I borrow your tape, man?

09:02.175 --> 09:04.143
- Matter of fact, I do mind.

09:09.580 --> 09:10.999
- Here you go.

09:11.785 --> 09:13.145
- Thanks, man.

09:22.198 --> 09:23.467
- Point.

09:37.165 --> 09:38.743
Point white.

09:49.653 --> 09:51.421
- Shouldn't block with your face.

09:54.661 --> 09:57.228
- His mama probably
didn't breast feed him.

09:57.835 --> 10:00.244
- Breast feeding is
actually very high in iron.

10:00.245 --> 10:02.223
I was very fond of it as a child.

10:02.503 --> 10:04.231
- I'm still fond of it.

10:04.656 --> 10:06.754
Sonny, Sonny Grasso.

10:06.763 --> 10:08.381
My friends call me Sonny.

10:08.372 --> 10:09.671
I'm Italian.

10:09.672 --> 10:11.191
- I'm Virgil Keller.

10:11.196 --> 10:14.282
I used to be Italian, now I'm a Buddhist.

10:15.468 --> 10:17.296
I'm just kidding, I was never Italian.

10:17.301 --> 10:18.990
- I knew that.

10:19.176 --> 10:21.544
- Sonny Grasso
and Travis Brickley,

10:21.542 --> 10:23.800
please report to ring three.

10:24.238 --> 10:26.915
- Look, the cowboy.

10:35.061 --> 10:37.709
- Have a nice day, knucklehead.

11:03.513 --> 11:05.141
- Point red.

11:05.164 --> 11:06.413
- What are you talking about?

11:06.410 --> 11:07.829
He hit me in the arm!

11:07.827 --> 11:09.425
He hit me in the arm.

11:11.982 --> 11:13.671
Are you blind?

11:16.298 --> 11:17.906
- Hey, it was a good fight.

11:25.685 --> 11:27.025
- We can fix that.

11:27.028 --> 11:28.497
He's a fighter.

12:05.239 --> 12:08.085
- I don't know about you
guys, but I'm impressed.

12:08.083 --> 12:11.150
Good lord, half the board
of directors are out there.

12:11.152 --> 12:12.571
They went completely nuts.

12:12.569 --> 12:14.467
Frank, believe me, you'll
get anything you need,

12:14.466 --> 12:15.465
first class.

12:15.468 --> 12:17.156
- I expect no less.

12:19.004 --> 12:20.903
This is your team.

12:25.231 --> 12:26.709
- Frank.

12:30.794 --> 12:35.199
Are you absolutely sure
about this kid Alex Grady?

12:35.226 --> 12:38.044
I saw him take quite a beating
a couple years back, Frank.

12:38.049 --> 12:39.998
And he's got a gimpy
shoulder, you know that.

12:40.000 --> 12:43.766
- Mr. Jennings, your
expertise is business.

12:43.760 --> 12:46.988
Mine is choosing and training champions.

12:46.990 --> 12:48.558
No offense.

13:02.877 --> 13:07.872
- On behalf of the sponsors,
the US Karate Federation,

13:08.599 --> 13:13.365
Coach Couzo and his staff,
it's my pleasure to announce

13:13.363 --> 13:18.357
the names of the five young
men who will represent

13:19.042 --> 13:23.727
the United States of America
in competition against

13:23.730 --> 13:25.718
Team Korea.

13:25.722 --> 13:28.299
When I announce your name, please rise

13:28.300 --> 13:30.628
and approach the podium.

13:32.977 --> 13:35.884
Travis Brickley, Miami, Florida.

13:38.434 --> 13:41.950
Virgil Keller, Providence, Rhode Island.

13:45.935 --> 13:49.063
Sonny Grasso, Detroit, Michigan.

13:50.730 --> 13:55.456
Thomas Lee, Fresno, California.

13:58.519 --> 14:00.486
And the final selection,

14:01.599 --> 14:05.305
Alexander Grady, Portland, Oregon.

14:07.726 --> 14:10.443
Congratulations, men, and welcome to the

14:10.443 --> 14:13.350
US National Team.

14:19.182 --> 14:21.440
- It's been a long time.

14:22.848 --> 14:23.677
How you doing?

14:23.679 --> 14:24.398
- How you doing?

14:24.403 --> 14:25.193
- Alexander Grady.

14:25.192 --> 14:25.980
- Tommy Lee.

14:27.704 --> 14:30.063
- Excuse me, fellas, fellas.

14:30.184 --> 14:31.383
Can I get...

14:31.382 --> 14:33.280
- At ease.

14:35.441 --> 14:39.288
Anybody not a member
of this team or staff.

14:39.681 --> 14:41.460
You are dismissed.

14:42.421 --> 14:44.899
Okay, listen.

14:46.555 --> 14:50.601
My name is Frank Couzo.

14:51.009 --> 14:56.004
To you I'm either Coach or Mr. Couzo.

14:58.244 --> 15:02.360
Starting tomorrow, you are mine

15:02.900 --> 15:05.118
for the next three months.

15:05.363 --> 15:10.357
That means no women, no alcohol, no drugs.

15:14.526 --> 15:19.271
You will eat, sleep, and shit competition.

15:19.885 --> 15:22.173
There are only two other rules.

15:23.359 --> 15:27.415
Number one, don't be late.

15:28.580 --> 15:30.977
Don't ever be late.

15:31.509 --> 15:35.955
It shows disrespect to me, to the sport,

15:36.348 --> 15:38.596
and to your teammates.

15:38.883 --> 15:43.279
Two, we expect you to function as a team.

15:44.191 --> 15:47.336
I'll say this only once.

15:48.740 --> 15:53.545
A team is not a team if
you don't give a damn

15:53.546 --> 15:55.674
about one another.

15:56.582 --> 16:01.578
You are now members of the
US National Karate Team.

16:02.634 --> 16:06.651
You represent the United
States of America.

16:06.971 --> 16:10.957
Remember that and we will
accomplish our objective.

16:11.052 --> 16:15.458
Our only objective, which is to win.

16:15.783 --> 16:16.553
- Yeah.

16:19.033 --> 16:20.372
- One more thing.

16:20.376 --> 16:22.054
When you get settled into night,

16:22.049 --> 16:24.177
Don will escort you into town.

16:24.180 --> 16:27.077
It's your last night in three months.

16:27.078 --> 16:30.305
If some of you are lucky,
you might even get laid.

16:31.863 --> 16:34.570
Knowing the high standards
of the local females,

16:34.569 --> 16:37.026
I seriously doubt it.

16:37.638 --> 16:42.623
But that bus leaves at 1900
hours sharp, gentlemen.

16:43.594 --> 16:45.092
- 1900 what?

16:45.086 --> 16:46.865
- 7:00 PM, pinhead.

16:46.866 --> 16:48.853
- I knew that.

16:49.976 --> 16:52.694
- Frank, there's somebody
I'd like you to meet.

16:52.694 --> 16:55.410
Someone I met last year
on a trip to the far east.

16:55.410 --> 16:57.878
Quite an extraordinary person, really.

16:57.872 --> 16:59.391
Trained in all kinds of things.

16:59.396 --> 17:02.193
Psychology, sports medicine, kinetics.

17:02.189 --> 17:05.224
Has a new book out now
on the power of the mind.

17:05.224 --> 17:08.071
Something of a sensei, actually.

17:08.079 --> 17:11.636
- Look, Mr. Jennings, I
was hired by the board

17:11.627 --> 17:13.955
to do a job and I intend to do it.

17:13.963 --> 17:16.130
- Nobody's questioning that, Frank.

17:16.125 --> 17:18.531
- I don't need any damn sensei.

17:20.760 --> 17:25.755
- Frank, there's a
trainer's position opening

17:27.598 --> 17:32.065
and we would like Wade
to fill that position.

17:32.928 --> 17:35.076
No offense.

17:38.174 --> 17:39.972
- I see.

17:47.375 --> 17:49.253
- Right this way, boys.

17:55.192 --> 17:57.170
- Oh, so sorry.

18:07.866 --> 18:09.574
- Well, this is us.

18:10.146 --> 18:11.434
- Is it okay if I take this one?

18:11.432 --> 18:13.451
- Yeah sure, man, go ahead.

18:26.086 --> 18:27.734
- You have a kid.

18:28.002 --> 18:29.691
- Yeah, well that's an old picture.

18:29.697 --> 18:31.554
Walter's five now.

18:31.551 --> 18:33.029
- Five going on 30, huh?

18:33.031 --> 18:34.479
- Yeah, how'd you know?

18:34.480 --> 18:37.078
- I work with kids, teaching.

18:37.656 --> 18:39.754
Your wife's very pretty.

18:40.065 --> 18:42.122
- Yeah, she was.

18:42.386 --> 18:44.484
She died when Walter was a baby.

18:44.725 --> 18:46.533
- I'm sorry.

18:47.681 --> 18:49.490
- Yeah, me too.

18:57.497 --> 18:59.924
- Man, this definitely ain't Detroit.

19:00.203 --> 19:01.522
- I never been to Detroit.

19:01.522 --> 19:02.641
What's it like?

19:02.641 --> 19:03.570
- What?

19:03.568 --> 19:05.435
- Detroit, what's it like?

19:05.443 --> 19:08.559
- Well, it's what you might call urban.

19:08.553 --> 19:10.242
It's kind of post urban,
you know, like those

19:10.248 --> 19:12.266
movies of Berlin after the war.

19:12.261 --> 19:14.370
Well that's the view out my window.

19:14.651 --> 19:15.820
- Ash tray?

19:15.819 --> 19:17.047
- Sure.

19:18.183 --> 19:19.811
You sure have a lot of gear, man.

19:19.814 --> 19:21.272
- What's that you say?

19:21.274 --> 19:22.043
- What?

19:22.041 --> 19:23.919
Oh, I said you sure have a lot of gear.

19:23.917 --> 19:25.395
- Oh gee, I got every major tournament

19:25.397 --> 19:26.675
the last five years.

19:26.675 --> 19:27.395
- Oh do you?

19:27.401 --> 19:28.020
- Right here.

19:28.018 --> 19:30.326
If you want statistics, lookie here.

19:30.320 --> 19:34.716
Hell, I got statistics on every
major fighter in the world.

19:34.721 --> 19:36.159
That's right.

19:36.159 --> 19:38.486
I'm something of a
collector, you might say.

19:38.481 --> 19:39.600
- Yeah, me too.

19:39.600 --> 19:41.369
Check this out.

19:43.635 --> 19:45.814
This is rare shit.

19:50.933 --> 19:52.511
- That's fantastic.

19:52.510 --> 19:54.199
That is fantastic.

19:59.916 --> 20:02.723
- Virgil, I've seen some
fine looking local snapper

20:02.719 --> 20:05.496
out there and I think they
could use some of this

20:05.500 --> 20:09.696
sweet Miami love muscle, if you
know what I'm talking about.

20:10.743 --> 20:11.901
Virgil, what the hell are you doing?

20:11.903 --> 20:13.531
You can do that for three months.

20:13.533 --> 20:15.061
We're talking about young things.

20:15.057 --> 20:17.944
We're talking about inner
and outer labia here.

20:18.680 --> 20:19.890
We're talking about the bus leaving if you

20:19.884 --> 20:21.143
don't get up and get dressed.

20:21.142 --> 20:22.910
You look like a pinata.

20:23.731 --> 20:26.428
Virgil, what are you going to do?

20:26.427 --> 20:28.504
Sit around and play with
your ball all night?

20:28.889 --> 20:30.127
Virgil.

20:31.766 --> 20:33.104
Virgil!

20:35.825 --> 20:38.593
All right, I'll go it alone.

20:45.095 --> 20:46.433
- Travis.

20:47.951 --> 20:51.268
Inner and outer labia?

21:13.630 --> 21:15.219
- Simple enough, Frank.

21:22.139 --> 21:23.647
- That's right.

21:40.999 --> 21:42.707
- You going number one or number two?

21:42.715 --> 21:44.243
- Drop dead.

21:48.818 --> 21:50.506
- Later, sport.

22:01.422 --> 22:03.020
- Excuse me.

22:03.169 --> 22:04.757
- I'm sorry!

22:04.906 --> 22:06.665
I've got a thing here.

22:06.718 --> 22:08.276
You all right, did it burn you?

22:08.273 --> 22:10.500
- No, no, it's okay.

22:10.499 --> 22:11.469
- Bartender, this isn't hot enough.

22:11.470 --> 22:13.547
Irish coffee is supposed to be hot.

22:13.878 --> 22:15.676
- What did he say?

22:16.880 --> 22:18.848
- I'm kidding.

22:20.175 --> 22:21.933
- I thought you were serious.

22:21.933 --> 22:23.331
- No, I'm Virgil.

22:23.328 --> 22:24.368
- Carol Anne.

22:24.374 --> 22:25.143
- Hi.

22:25.141 --> 22:25.990
- Hi.

22:25.993 --> 22:27.681
- Carol Anne.

22:28.379 --> 22:29.798
- Would you like to dance?

22:29.797 --> 22:31.366
- I'd love to.

22:31.608 --> 22:32.917
- Good.

22:36.851 --> 22:39.289
- You burned her hand
and she'd love to dance?

23:08.921 --> 23:10.499
- Want to dance?

23:11.418 --> 23:12.417
- Love to.

23:12.414 --> 23:14.102
- Well let's go.

23:22.340 --> 23:23.378
- Nothing.

23:23.383 --> 23:24.173
Nothing.

23:24.173 --> 23:25.011
Vodka.

23:25.014 --> 23:26.223
- Vodka.

23:26.219 --> 23:27.488
- How you doing this evening?

23:27.486 --> 23:29.374
- I don't understand it, man.

23:29.373 --> 23:30.481
- What?

23:30.480 --> 23:32.448
- I mean, women love me.

23:33.160 --> 23:34.509
- Not tonight.

23:34.508 --> 23:35.038
- What?

23:35.041 --> 23:36.989
- Not tonight they don't.

23:36.991 --> 23:38.609
- Yeah, but I'm Italian.

23:38.610 --> 23:40.508
- You know, well Virgil's doing great.

23:40.507 --> 23:43.084
Maybe you should become a Buddhist.

23:46.335 --> 23:48.564
- What could they be talking about?

23:48.563 --> 23:50.760
- Buddha.

23:51.344 --> 23:53.781
- It's one of those
conditioned automatic response

23:53.784 --> 23:55.593
patterns that just gets in the way of our

23:55.584 --> 23:57.373
natural abilities, you know?

23:57.374 --> 23:58.633
- I know.

24:00.491 --> 24:02.039
- Sweet bellybutton.

24:02.042 --> 24:03.550
I'm going to give it a shot.

24:05.015 --> 24:07.563
- He's a dog, an absolute dog.

24:14.413 --> 24:18.079
- Hey Burt, you might want
to check the dance floor.

