your son is in a coma.

50:16.305 --> 50:18.073
There appear to be no other complications,

50:18.073 --> 50:20.271
but I must tell you he
could remain unconscious

50:20.268 --> 50:22.306
for an hour or a month.

50:22.335 --> 50:23.315
- Oh my god.

50:23.316 --> 50:24.784
I want to see him.

50:43.167 --> 50:44.735
Walter.

50:47.504 --> 50:49.542
Walter, can you hear me?

50:50.956 --> 50:52.845
It's daddy.

50:54.647 --> 50:56.634
Daddy's here.

51:01.494 --> 51:03.252
Walter.

51:04.207 --> 51:06.105
Don't leave me.

51:08.756 --> 51:10.704
I need you.

51:49.845 --> 51:51.283
Walter?

51:56.056 --> 51:58.394
- I crashed myself.

51:59.103 --> 52:01.131
- Yes you did.

52:02.599 --> 52:04.427
We're here, Walter.

52:04.804 --> 52:06.763
We're right here.

52:08.682 --> 52:10.430
That's my boy.

52:15.692 --> 52:16.880
- Recoil, Travis.

52:16.872 --> 52:18.691
- Okay Travis, go for it.

52:20.643 --> 52:23.290
- It's 57 mile per hour,
195 pounds pressure.

52:23.284 --> 52:24.833
That's pretty good, Brick.

52:24.841 --> 52:26.519
- One more time, Travis.

52:26.514 --> 52:27.932
- Coach.

52:27.930 --> 52:29.369
- Don't bother, Grady,
you're off the team.

52:29.369 --> 52:30.827
- I need to talk to you for a minute.

52:30.829 --> 52:32.598
- Nothing to talk about,
Grady, you made your choice.

52:32.598 --> 52:34.985
- Coach, I caught the first plane back.

52:35.574 --> 52:38.551
I had to go, can't you understand that?

52:43.349 --> 52:45.536
Well, do you want me to beg?

52:47.377 --> 52:48.596
Do you want me to...

52:48.592 --> 52:50.160
Hey Frank!

52:51.714 --> 52:53.781
You want me to beg?

52:54.079 --> 52:55.307
Okay.

52:59.690 --> 53:01.448
I will beg.

53:03.467 --> 53:05.334
I need this.

53:05.874 --> 53:10.100
This is the only thing
I know I am good at.

53:11.628 --> 53:16.124
Don't take that away from me, please.

53:24.574 --> 53:26.263
- Don, line up the alternate.

53:26.267 --> 53:28.135
Who's next, Tommy?

53:37.761 --> 53:39.270
Tommy.

53:52.275 --> 53:55.272
- 53 mile per hour, 184 pounds pressure.

53:55.269 --> 53:56.847
- Where the hell do
you think you're going?

53:56.845 --> 53:58.483
We leave for the tournament in two days.

53:58.486 --> 54:00.205
You're still pulling punches.

54:00.202 --> 54:02.130
Holding back won't change a damn thing.

54:02.129 --> 54:05.166
If you want to be here,
you've got to give us 100%,

54:05.165 --> 54:06.483
no less.

54:06.486 --> 54:07.975
Now do it again.

54:08.320 --> 54:09.258
- Coach.

54:09.268 --> 54:11.426
- I said do it again.

54:28.799 --> 54:30.298
Do it!

54:41.191 --> 54:42.020
- Is he okay?

54:42.022 --> 54:43.480
- Don't know yet.

54:43.674 --> 54:45.053
Pulse is okay.

54:45.059 --> 54:46.588
Breathing.

55:03.461 --> 55:05.629
- Virgil, Virgil.

55:05.826 --> 55:06.895
- Hey, hey.

55:06.892 --> 55:08.251
Big stretch.

55:08.607 --> 55:10.185
- Hey, how are you, man?

55:10.184 --> 55:12.253
- He's just taking a break.

55:16.397 --> 55:17.326
- Tommy!

55:17.324 --> 55:18.942
- Let him go.

55:20.041 --> 55:21.379
- Virgil.

55:23.034 --> 55:24.764
He's all right.

55:25.261 --> 55:27.669
Virgil, you know where you are?

55:27.745 --> 55:29.943
Do you know where you are?

55:32.146 --> 55:33.884
- On the floor.

55:35.214 --> 55:38.081
- Hey, hey where you going?

55:39.000 --> 55:40.358
- How's your kid, Alex?

55:40.360 --> 55:41.779
- He's gonna be okay, thank god.

55:41.778 --> 55:42.817
Where are you going?

55:42.822 --> 55:44.121
- I'm quitting the team.

55:44.122 --> 55:45.450
- Bullshit.

55:45.444 --> 55:46.772
Why?

55:47.457 --> 55:48.576
- Because I can't fight Dae Han.

55:48.576 --> 55:49.185
- Why?

55:49.183 --> 55:51.431
- Because I can't fight Dae Han.

55:51.431 --> 55:53.679
- What are you talking about, man?

55:58.059 --> 56:01.776
- Dae Han killed my
brother in a tournament

56:01.778 --> 56:03.876
just like this one.

56:05.274 --> 56:07.721
- Why didn't you ever tell me this?

56:07.809 --> 56:08.898
- It wasn't your problem.

56:08.896 --> 56:10.284
- That's bullshit, man.

56:10.281 --> 56:11.441
- What do you want me to say?

56:11.443 --> 56:12.721
- Say something.

56:12.721 --> 56:14.479
- I want to kill the son of a bitch.

56:14.479 --> 56:15.839
- Then kill the son of a bitch.

56:15.833 --> 56:17.521
- Alex!

56:18.547 --> 56:20.755
I'm afraid.

56:22.586 --> 56:25.083
If you don't deal with this right now,

56:26.059 --> 56:27.928
you never will.

56:28.170 --> 56:30.936
You'll just shove it inside like I did.

56:30.983 --> 56:34.949
Melissa died and I just packed it in.

56:34.946 --> 56:39.161
I took all that pain
and I just packed it in.

56:40.721 --> 56:42.640
I was wrong.

56:43.322 --> 56:46.119
You are wrong.

56:47.381 --> 56:49.499
Your brother is gone, man.

56:49.555 --> 56:53.392
Melissa is gone.

56:56.265 --> 56:58.443
You need this fight bad.

56:58.442 --> 57:00.490
You need this fight for you, man.

57:00.488 --> 57:02.635
This is your chance.

57:03.549 --> 57:05.198
Don't blow it.

57:06.759 --> 57:08.447
That's all I got to say.

57:08.592 --> 57:10.690
Except you're an asshole.

57:35.689 --> 57:37.446
- Hey, what are you doing
in Coach Couzo's office?

57:37.446 --> 57:38.825
You're not supposed to be doing that.

57:38.821 --> 57:39.610
- What is it, Don?

57:39.609 --> 57:41.157
What is it I don't know?

57:41.166 --> 57:43.024
- I don't have the faintest
idea what you're talking about.

57:43.019 --> 57:44.827
- What is it about Tommy?

57:46.354 --> 57:47.473
- Look, I really think
you should leave here

57:47.473 --> 57:48.932
before Coach Couzo gets back.

57:48.933 --> 57:51.410
- Don, there's two pages
missing from Tommy's file.

57:51.416 --> 57:53.133
- Yeah, that's right, I can't discuss it.

57:53.131 --> 57:54.380
Look, I really think you should...

57:54.378 --> 57:56.397
- I'm not leaving until you tell me.

57:56.400 --> 57:57.349
- Oh boy.

57:57.347 --> 57:58.835
- You're not responsible for this.

57:58.838 --> 58:00.876
- Look, I know I'm not
responsible for this, Miss Wade,

58:00.873 --> 58:03.071
I just could lose my job because of it.

58:05.072 --> 58:08.249
Now, you did not get that from me, right?

58:08.343 --> 58:11.100
No, no, come on now, you
didn't get that from me.

58:13.841 --> 58:17.986
You know the enemy
is waiting in the ring

58:19.709 --> 58:23.176
Fate is riding on the fight

58:27.296 --> 58:31.581
You'll have to find a
way to keep a good man down

58:32.815 --> 58:36.791
He'll take the challenge
on with all his might

58:40.536 --> 58:44.981
Though a little part
is burning in his soul

58:46.358 --> 58:50.454
The thought of it is
heavy on your mind

58:57.632 --> 58:59.021
- Pick it up.

58:59.026 --> 59:00.704
- Why didn't you tell me about Tommy?

59:00.699 --> 59:02.647
This is how you deal
with people, Mr. Couzo.

59:02.648 --> 59:03.617
- What are you talking about?

59:03.618 --> 59:04.638
- You know what I'm talking about.

59:04.641 --> 59:06.029
I've just seen the videotape.

59:08.015 --> 59:09.233
- So?

59:09.230 --> 59:10.590
- So?

59:10.594 --> 59:12.961
How could you send him
to the ring with Dae Han?

59:12.959 --> 59:14.448
- Because Tommy's the
only fighter on this team

59:14.452 --> 59:16.780
who has a chance against
him and you know it.

59:16.775 --> 59:19.143
- So it's only about
winning then, is that it?

59:19.141 --> 59:21.149
Win at any cost, right coach?

59:21.154 --> 59:22.383
- Back off, Wade.

59:22.379 --> 59:23.378
I don't have to listen to this.

59:23.381 --> 59:24.470
- Yes you do, Frank.

59:24.468 --> 59:26.167
If you pull one more
stunt like you just pulled

59:26.163 --> 59:27.601
with Tommy, you won't
have to get on a plane

59:27.601 --> 59:30.938
because I will personally kick
your ass from here to Korea.

59:34.219 --> 59:36.656
None of this had to happen, Frank.

59:37.257 --> 59:39.934
Did you ever stop to think
what it might be like

59:39.929 --> 59:42.247
if you cared as much about these guys

59:42.251 --> 59:44.270
as you do about winning?

59:44.276 --> 59:47.074
- This has nothing to do with winning.

59:47.654 --> 59:50.492
If those boys do their best and fail,

59:50.489 --> 59:52.496
I'll still be proud.

59:52.811 --> 59:54.450
But if they don't give me their all

59:54.452 --> 59:56.590
and if I don't give them mine,

59:56.583 --> 01:00:00.220
that is my failure and my disgrace.

01:00:01.922 --> 01:00:04.739
Matter of fact, that's
exactly what happened

01:00:04.735 --> 01:00:06.373
to Tommy's brother.

01:00:06.375 --> 01:00:08.464
You saw that tape.

01:00:09.523 --> 01:00:11.941
I was the coach of that team, Miss Wade.

01:00:12.556 --> 01:00:15.564
I carried the burden of
his death for 15 years.

01:00:16.563 --> 01:00:18.480
Those boys didn't know what
they were getting into.

01:00:18.489 --> 01:00:19.936
I did.

01:00:20.672 --> 01:00:22.850
It was all just a game to them.

01:00:23.731 --> 01:00:26.638
I didn't know enough
then to give them rules,

01:00:26.639 --> 01:00:28.777
to drive them to the edge,
to the breaking point,

01:00:28.771 --> 01:00:30.729
to where they hated my guts.

01:00:30.998 --> 01:00:34.833
Tommy's brother died because I failed.

01:00:35.750 --> 01:00:38.088
He was not prepared.

01:00:38.786 --> 01:00:43.293
And I will never let
that happen again, ever.

01:01:04.818 --> 01:01:05.917
- Coach.

01:01:06.735 --> 01:01:09.493
We, um, we need to talk to you.

01:01:11.125 --> 01:01:12.704
- I'm listening.

01:01:15.601 --> 01:01:19.936
- Coach, um, we all thought that...

01:01:19.935 --> 01:01:21.864
- What is it, Grasso?

01:01:22.236 --> 01:01:24.384
- Well, we uh...

01:01:24.390 --> 01:01:26.877
- We hope you change your mind about Alex.

01:01:26.872 --> 01:01:28.010
- Since when did you give a rat's ass

01:01:28.013 --> 01:01:29.731
about anybody but you?

01:01:29.728 --> 01:01:31.296
- Since now.

01:01:33.319 --> 01:01:35.885
Coach, we need Alex

01:01:36.942 --> 01:01:39.549
and we need Tommy to win.

01:01:41.320 --> 01:01:42.808
- That all?

01:01:44.176 --> 01:01:45.515
- Yes sir.

01:01:45.871 --> 01:01:48.678
- Plane leaves tomorrow, 2000 hours.

01:01:58.026 --> 01:01:59.954
I'll be damned.

01:02:10.653 --> 01:02:12.292
- May I come in?

01:02:12.453 --> 01:02:14.031
Mr. Jennings, if you're going to fire me,

01:02:14.030 --> 01:02:15.309
then damn it, fire me.

01:02:15.309 --> 01:02:17.027
- Nobody's firing you yet.

01:02:17.933 --> 01:02:19.972
- Until I am relieved of my duties,

01:02:19.976 --> 01:02:22.254
I'll continue to make all decisions

01:02:22.246 --> 01:02:25.443
concerning the conduct of
this team as I see fit.

01:02:29.045 --> 01:02:30.893
- Great, you're back!

01:02:33.658 --> 01:02:36.005
- That includes the
participation of Alex Grady.

01:02:36.009 --> 01:02:37.848
I have a lot to do before we leave, so

01:02:37.843 --> 01:02:39.610
if you don't mind.

01:03:36.669 --> 01:03:38.497
- Come on, boys, hop in.

01:03:49.023 --> 01:03:50.342
- You, Coach.

01:03:50.521 --> 01:03:51.759
- Tickets.

01:03:51.768 --> 01:03:53.056
- This way.

01:03:53.280 --> 01:03:54.758
Travis.

01:03:54.922 --> 01:03:55.971
Where's Virgil?

01:03:55.966 --> 01:03:57.514
- He's in the bathroom.

01:03:58.939 --> 01:04:00.617
- Hey, what do you think?

01:04:00.620 --> 01:04:01.878
- About what?

01:04:01.876 --> 01:04:03.754
- He shaved his beard.

01:04:03.759 --> 01:04:05.678
- It'll make me faster, don't you think?

01:04:05.958 --> 01:04:07.667
- Yeah.

01:04:14.585 --> 01:04:16.294
- Tommy!

01:04:17.719 --> 01:04:18.807
- Coach, I, uh...

01:04:18.805 --> 01:04:21.403
- No apologies offered or accepted.

01:04:22.407 --> 01:04:23.875
Welcome back.

01:04:26.945 --> 01:04:29.002
- Thank you, sir.

01:04:29.363 --> 01:04:30.681
Yeah!

01:04:31.100 --> 01:04:32.119
Hey, Virgil.

01:04:32.123 --> 01:04:33.132
- I'm all right.

01:04:33.124 --> 01:04:33.994
- I'm glad you're all right.

01:04:33.998 --> 01:04:35.177
- You kick hard.

01:04:36.757 --> 01:04:37.997
- Hey buddy, how you doing?

01:04:37.995 --> 01:04:39.523
- Here's your coat.

01:04:40.876 --> 01:04:42.195
- I owe you one.

01:04:42.203 --> 01:04:43.172
- Yeah you do.

01:04:43.172 --> 01:04:44.331
- Yeah.

01:04:45.655 --> 01:04:46.814
- It's good to have you back.

01:04:46.817 --> 01:04:48.235
- Good to be here.

01:04:48.231 --> 01:04:50.379
Sonny, Miss Wade.

01:04:52.472 --> 01:04:53.960
Travis.

01:05:23.232 --> 01:05:25.679
- Hello everybody, I'm
Ahmad Rashad and welcome

01:05:25.672 --> 01:05:28.489
to Seoul, Korea and the Jamsil gymnasium

01:05:28.496 --> 01:05:30.054
for an invitation tournament between the

01:05:30.051 --> 01:05:32.079
national teams of the Republic of Korea

01:05:32.075 --> 01:05:33.594
and the United States.

01:05:33.600 --> 01:05:35.827
This afternoon we'll be
watching the United States

01:05:35.826 --> 01:05:39.243
team under the leadership
of Coach Frank Couzo,

01:05:39.247 --> 01:05:41.415
himself a veteran of
this often perilous sport

01:05:41.410 --> 01:05:43.757
leading his youthful warriors
in a sport traditionally

01:05:43.753 --> 01:05:46.501
dominated by Asian powerhouses.

01:06:02.107 --> 01:06:05.344
- You've worked
very hard, all of you.

01:06:05.949 --> 01:06:09.846
You've grown as athletes and individuals.

01:06:10.542 --> 01:06:12.030
You've learned a lot.

01:06:12.428 --> 01:06:14.735
We've all learned a lot.

01:06:15.550 --> 01:06:17.838
As Catherine might say, the teacher also

01:06:17.830 --> 01:06:19.808
learns from the students.

01:06:20.675 --> 01:06:23.142
Today you have a chance to be the best

01:06:23.136 --> 01:06:25.644
martial artists in the world.

01:06:26.248 --> 01:06:27.876
It's up to you.

01:06:30.820 --> 01:06:34.576
If you give everything
you've got, everything

01:06:34.580 --> 01:06:38.407
with all your heart, you'll be winners.

01:06:39.173 --> 01:06:41.021
That I promise you.

01:06:42.284 --> 01:06:45.221
You can be the best of the best.

01:06:55.060 --> 01:06:58.107
- A capacity
crowd of 15,000 spectators

01:06:58.107 --> 01:07:00.795
has jammed Jamsil arena
for this traditional

01:07:00.793 --> 01:07:03.740
sporting event which is
held every three years.

01:07:04.106 --> 01:07:06.174
The pageantry you are witnessing shows the

01:07:06.174 --> 01:07:08.542
importance of Tae Kwon
Do to Korean heritage.

01:07:08.540 --> 01:07:11.767
They are as passionate
and wild about Tae Kwon Do

01:07:11.768 --> 01:07:14.125
as the Americans are about baseball.

01:07:37.096 --> 01:07:38.415
- And here they come
now, the United States

01:07:38.417 --> 01:07:41.154
national team, Coach
Couzo and the assistant

01:07:41.155 --> 01:07:43.643
coaches Catherine Wade and Don Peterson.

01:08:05.876 --> 01:08:07.984
- Grandma, I see him!

01:08:41.752 --> 01:08:43.310
- And now the Korean national team

01:08:43.308 --> 01:08:44.787
makes its entrance.

01:10:05.766 --> 01:10:07.264
- For you viewers new to the sport,

01:10:07.268 --> 01:10:09.066
this is a full contact match,

01:10:09.058 --> 01:10:11.026
the object of which is to win points or

01:10:11.029 --> 01:10:12.677
knock out your opponent.

01:10:12.681 --> 01:10:15.139
Styles include a
combination of Tae Kwon Do,

01:10:15.132 --> 01:10:17.629
Karate, Judo, and kickboxing.

01:10:17.635 --> 01:10:19.914
Each match consists of
three two minute rounds

01:10:19.916 --> 01:10:23.073
with accumulated points
added to both side's totals.

01:10:24.253 --> 01:10:25.711
- Hey Coach Wade.

01:10:26.281 --> 01:10:28.579
What's my son doing here?

01:10:32.233 --> 01:10:33.743
Thank you.

01:10:37.125 --> 01:10:39.033
- We now direct your
attention to center stage

01:10:39.032 --> 01:10:41.120
for the first match of the afternoon.

01:10:41.120 --> 01:10:44.036
Yung Kim of Korea versus Sonny Grasso, a

01:10:44.040 --> 01:10:47.147
second degree black belt
hailing from Detroit, Michigan.

01:10:47.310 --> 01:10:50.068
Our referee is Mr. Chang
Park Kim, a veteran of the

01:10:50.071 --> 01:10:52.528
Korean Tae Kwon Do Association.

01:11:02.548 --> 01:11:04.377
And it looks like we're
about to get underway.

01:11:04.380 --> 01:11:06.669
The Americans heavy
underdogs against their

01:11:06.661 --> 01:11:08.620
Asian counterparts.

01:11:16.241 --> 01:11:17.090
- Come on, Sonny.

01:11:17.093 --> 01:11:17.702
- Come on, Sonny.

01:11:17.700 --> 01:11:18.740
- Come on!

01:11:26.393 --> 01:11:28.101
- Power counter!

01:11:32.914 --> 01:11:34.442
- Point good!

01:11:37.111 --> 01:11:38.500
- Here in the
third and final round,

01:11:38.507 --> 01:11:41.784
Grasso is beginning to
fade, Yung Kim relentless.

01:11:42.318 --> 01:11:45.334
He lands with a vicious
jump spinning back kick!

01:11:51.177 --> 01:11:52.745
Grasso is down.

01:12:03.570 --> 01:12:05.268
Korea takes the first match.

01:12:05.263 --> 01:12:08.690
The score stands Korea 11,
the United States seven.

01:12:10.356 --> 01:12:12.615
Here in round three,
Virgil Keller capitalizing

01:12:12.616 --> 01:12:15.961
on his speed and scores with
a spinning roundhouse kick.

01:12:41.694 --> 01:12:44.372
An elbow to the spine
and Keller is down again.

01:12:44.369 --> 01:12:46.127
- Come on, Virgil!

01:12:46.777 --> 01:12:48.745
- He appears to be dazed.

01:12:48.982 --> 01:12:51.659
- Stay focused, stay focused!

01:12:59.840 --> 01:13:01.988
- That is the
end of the second match.

01:13:01.993 --> 01:13:04.810
The winner, Han Cho, giving
the Republic of Korea

01:13:04.806 --> 01:13:08.802
a total of 20 points
against nine for the USA.

01:13:10.207 --> 01:13:11.966
It's not a pretty sight,
ladies and gentlemen.

01:13:11.966 --> 01:13:13.304
Both fighters bloody.

01:13:13.308 --> 01:13:14.986
Travis Brickley of the
United States going on

01:13:14.982 --> 01:13:17.179
every last ounce of strength as he fights

01:13:17.188 --> 01:13:19.135
blow for blow with a seemingly exhausted

01:13:19.136 --> 01:13:20.735
Tung Sung Moon.

01:13:32.872 --> 01:13:34.660
- Come on, come on!

01:13:34.657 --> 01:13:35.567
Come on!

01:13:39.878 --> 01:13:42.375
- This partisan
crowd showing disapproval

01:13:42.382 --> 01:13:44.160
of Brickley's conduct.

01:13:47.308 --> 01:13:49.436
- Travis, behave yourself!

01:13:50.683 --> 01:13:52.222
- It's a full count, kimchi, and I'm going

01:13:52.218 --> 01:13:53.816
to hit home run on your fase, boy.

01:13:53.816 --> 01:13:55.484
- This might be exactly
what Brickley needed

01:13:55.484 --> 01:13:56.753
to fire him up.

01:13:56.752 --> 01:13:58.660
He scores heavily with a quick and sending

01:13:58.659 --> 01:13:59.998
Moon to the canvas.

01:14:00.002 --> 01:14:01.670
It should be a score.

01:14:01.674 --> 01:14:03.622
Yes, it's all time of the three piece.

01:14:03.615 --> 01:14:05.363
An incredible comeback from Brickley.

01:14:05.361 --> 01:14:07.320
- USA!

01:14:13.427 --> 01:14:15.255
- A demonstration of
strength will determine the

01:14:15.260 --> 01:14:18.538
winner of the Travis Brickley,
Tung Sung Moon match.

01:14:18.531 --> 01:14:20.300
The fighter breaking
the most bricks will be

01:14:20.300 --> 01:14:22.448
declared the victor.

01:14:58.967 --> 01:15:01.265
- It appears as
though Tung Sung Moon

01:15:01.257 --> 01:15:03.755
is using a very unorthodox technique,

01:15:03.761 --> 01:15:05.939
something called the ridge hand.

01:15:30.049 --> 01:15:32.866
- What are you counting them for?

01:15:34.875 --> 01:15:36.633
- Only one
concrete block separates

01:15:36.633 --> 01:15:38.791
the fate of Brickley and Moon.

01:15:39.233 --> 01:15:40.182
- Tung.

01:15:40.181 --> 01:15:42.229
- But the match
goes to Tung Sung Moon.

01:15:42.227 --> 01:15:44.655
Now remember, this is a team competition

01:15:44.657 --> 01:15:46.865
where total points rather than individual

01:15:46.863 --> 01:15:49.890
match scores decide the overall winner.

01:15:50.784 --> 01:15:53.061
Coming up next, another
long shot, the veteran

01:15:53.053 --> 01:15:57.040
fighter on the team from
Portland, Oregon, Alex Grady.

01:16:01.865 --> 01:16:05.411
- Alex, it's up to you and me.

01:16:05.509 --> 01:16:07.188
You and me.

01:16:07.492 --> 01:16:10.090
- We're taking home the gold, Tommy.

01:16:10.986 --> 01:16:12.046
Yeah!

01:16:12.052 --> 01:16:13.491
- Do it!

01:16:13.491 --> 01:16:15.169
- This is a
real test for Alex Grady

01:16:15.164 --> 01:16:17.031
after a three year layoff
from the tournament

01:16:17.039 --> 01:16:18.997
circuit he makes his comeback against

01:16:18.989 --> 01:16:21.467
Sae Jin Kwon, considered to be the top

01:16:21.471 --> 01:16:23.949
ranking fighter in his weight class.

01:16:25.670 --> 01:16:26.899
- Watch the shoulder.

01:16:26.895 --> 01:16:27.944
You can take him, Alex.

01:16:27.939 --> 01:16:28.938
You've got the tools.

01:16:28.941 --> 01:16:29.660
- Yes sir.

01:16:29.665 --> 01:16:31.183
- Go get 'em.

01:16:35.992 --> 01:16:37.510
- This crowd is
really into this one,

01:16:37.516 --> 01:16:40.963
anticipating a major
battle between these two

01:16:40.957 --> 01:16:42.756
tough competitors.

01:16:45.923 --> 01:16:48.510
- I'm gonna kick your ass.

01:16:57.772 --> 01:16:59.001
- And here we go.

01:16:59.000 --> 01:17:00.708
Alex Grady measuring.

01:17:01.184 --> 01:17:03.592
Sae Jin Kwon attacks,
Grady counters with a down

01:17:03.592 --> 01:17:05.051
and scores.

01:17:05.170 --> 01:17:06.848
- Down, down, down!

01:17:06.843 --> 01:17:08.431
- For you, Travis.

01:17:08.579 --> 01:17:09.778
- Take that.

01:17:11.911 --> 01:17:14.359
- The Korean bounces right back.

01:17:15.327 --> 01:17:17.855
A point for the Korean team.

01:17:24.331 --> 01:17:26.009
In the earlier matches
today, the Koreans have

01:17:26.004 --> 01:17:28.711
built up a wide lead, but
because of this outstanding

01:17:28.710 --> 01:17:30.919
performance by Alex Grady, the Americans

01:17:30.917 --> 01:17:32.466
are closing the gap.

01:17:35.393 --> 01:17:38.749
But it is way too early
to write off Sae Jin Kwon.

01:17:51.354 --> 01:17:53.093
As we approach the end of round two,

01:17:53.091 --> 01:17:55.648
this match is really starting to heat up.

01:17:56.043 --> 01:17:58.560
Ooh, Sae Jin Kwon explodes with a vicious

01:17:58.567 --> 01:18:00.305
aerial back knuckle.

01:18:02.233 --> 01:18:04.441
As if this physical
confrontation weren't enough,

01:18:04.440 --> 01:18:07.036
he seems to be taunting Grady.

01:18:17.244 --> 01:18:18.563
- You're mine.

01:18:29.601 --> 01:18:31.390
- No, no!

01:18:38.965 --> 01:18:41.492
- The athletes are
starting to lose their composure.

01:18:41.490 --> 01:18:43.907
Clearly both teams are
more determined to win,

01:18:43.908 --> 01:18:46.756
but that determination
doesn't affect the score.

01:18:46.785 --> 01:18:49.153
Alex Grady has thus far
defied the odds and is

01:18:49.151 --> 01:18:51.020
leading in the second
heaviest weight class

01:18:51.025 --> 01:18:52.633
of the competition.

01:18:57.425 --> 01:18:59.863
- Alex, when he comes in,

01:18:59.866 --> 01:19:02.723
side step and use your ridge hand.

01:19:03.063 --> 01:19:05.041
You're going to use your distance.

01:19:05.033 --> 01:19:07.072
Set him up and sweep him.

01:19:07.165 --> 01:19:08.024
- Yes sir.

01:19:08.027 --> 01:19:08.686
- Take it to him.

01:19:08.678 --> 01:19:09.777
- Yes sir.

01:19:21.408 --> 01:19:24.046
I'm gonna take your head off.

01:19:37.060 --> 01:19:38.609
Thank you, folks.

01:19:42.877 --> 01:19:44.155
- With one minute remaining in the

01:19:44.155 --> 01:19:46.333
third round, both
athletes are landing some

01:19:46.340 --> 01:19:48.706
incredible combinations,
although neither fighter

01:19:48.705 --> 01:19:51.292
seems able to seize the advantage.

01:20:01.641 --> 01:20:03.449
Grady is down.

01:20:03.961 --> 01:20:05.550
He's hurt.

01:20:08.951 --> 01:20:11.290
An injured shoulder forced Grady into

01:20:11.294 --> 01:20:12.623
retirement three years ago.

01:20:12.616 --> 01:20:15.963
It now appears he's re-injured
that very same shoulder.

01:20:18.785 --> 01:20:20.824
What a blow for the Americans.

01:20:20.821 --> 01:20:22.519
Alex Grady, hurt.

01:20:22.515 --> 01:20:24.952
If he can't continue,
the match will be forfeit

01:20:24.954 --> 01:20:26.963
and the American team
will lose the valuable

01:20:26.969 --> 01:20:29.356
points that Grady's earned so far.

01:20:29.473 --> 01:20:30.892
- You want to quit now?

01:20:30.890 --> 01:20:32.258
- No, I don't know.

01:20:32.254 --> 01:20:33.643
- Two minutes.

01:20:33.650 --> 01:20:34.808
Two minutes.

01:20:34.810 --> 01:20:37.178
- Pop it, pop it, pop it.

01:20:37.176 --> 01:20:39.034
- Listen here, Alexander,
we can't let you go on.

01:20:39.030 --> 01:20:40.099
Your shoulder's dislocated.

01:20:40.096 --> 01:20:41.605
We're going to have to stop
this thing, right coach?

01:20:41.608 --> 01:20:42.657
- You did your best, Alex.

01:20:42.654 --> 01:20:43.782
Catherine, take him to medical.

01:20:43.782 --> 01:20:44.781
- No!

01:20:44.784 --> 01:20:45.754
Pop it, Tommy.

01:20:45.754 --> 01:20:47.332
Shit, Tommy, pop it!

01:20:47.331 --> 01:20:48.979
- Forget it, Alex, it's over.

01:20:48.982 --> 01:20:51.900
- Do it! Do it! Do it!

01:20:58.541 --> 01:20:59.809
- Grandma!

01:20:59.820 --> 01:21:01.089
- God damn it!

01:21:01.088 --> 01:21:02.526
Tape it up, tape it up.

01:21:02.526 --> 01:21:04.234
If I'm out, it's over.

01:21:04.241 --> 01:21:05.640
I can hold him off or 30 seconds.

01:21:05.636 --> 01:21:08.074
God damn it, I said tape it up!

01:21:08.120 --> 01:21:09.369
- Ladies and
gentlemen, I've just been

01:21:09.367 --> 01:21:10.755
informed that there will
be a two minute injury

01:21:10.763 --> 01:21:13.620
time out to determine if
Alex Grady can continue.

01:21:13.618 --> 01:21:15.546
Now there's just 30
seconds left on the clock.

01:21:15.547 --> 01:21:17.605
If he can hold on, he keeps the points

01:21:17.603 --> 01:21:19.821
and the Americans are still in it.

01:21:20.022 --> 01:21:22.220
- Put your mind somewhere else.

01:21:22.217 --> 01:21:24.166
Let the pain go.

01:21:24.168 --> 01:21:26.085
There is no pain.

01:21:26.926 --> 01:21:28.875
There is no pain.

01:21:28.992 --> 01:21:30.959
- You got 30 seconds to go, Alex.

01:21:31.153 --> 01:21:33.142
You go out and do it.

01:21:33.792 --> 01:21:35.060
Let's get up.

01:21:39.194 --> 01:21:40.333
- Yeah!

01:21:40.334 --> 01:21:41.773
- This is unbelievable.

01:21:41.773 --> 01:21:43.231
What a show of courage.

01:21:43.232 --> 01:21:45.350
Alex Grady has reentered the ring.

01:21:45.342 --> 01:21:47.840
He intends to finish this fight.

01:21:58.075 --> 01:22:00.383
And Kwon immediately
attacks the left shoulder.

01:22:00.377 --> 01:22:02.325
Alex bravely pairing with his left hand,

01:22:02.327 --> 01:22:04.095
trying to keep Kwon at bay.

01:22:05.108 --> 01:22:07.785
Kwon attacks, Grady counters and scores.

01:22:09.349 --> 01:22:11.417
Oh, and Grady catches him with a jumping

01:22:11.416 --> 01:22:13.474
front kick that knocks Kwon!

01:22:13.481 --> 01:22:14.809
- Yes sir!

01:22:18.308 --> 01:22:19.577
- Yeah!

01:22:20.418 --> 01:22:21.556
- The buzzers sound.

01:22:21.557 --> 01:22:23.276
That is the end of the match.

01:22:23.273 --> 01:22:25.751
Alex Grady, injured shoulder and all,

01:22:25.756 --> 01:22:28.104
has defeated Sae Jin Kwon and managed

01:22:28.100 --> 01:22:30.268
to keep the American hopes alive.

01:22:31.893 --> 01:22:34.000
Ladies and gentlemen,
we direct your attention

01:22:33.994 --> 01:22:36.980
to center ring for the final
match of the afternoon.

01:22:36.988 --> 01:22:41.033
Representing Korea at 175
pounds, the winner of the

01:22:41.025 --> 01:22:44.032
gold medals at the 1984 through the 1988

01:22:44.042 --> 01:22:47.198
world games, Dae Han Park.

01:22:48.026 --> 01:22:51.582
For the United States team at 167 pounds,

01:22:51.575 --> 01:22:54.402
winner of a gold medal
at the 1988 invitational

01:22:54.409 --> 01:22:58.695
championship, from Fresno,
California, Tommy Lee.

01:23:02.270 --> 01:23:03.589
- Tommy.

01:23:05.779 --> 01:23:06.989
- Yes sir?

01:23:07.779 --> 01:23:09.168
- Don't hold back.

01:23:09.175 --> 01:23:10.504
You can do it.

01:23:10.496 --> 01:23:11.904
- Yes sir.

01:23:20.491 --> 01:23:22.109
- And there's Dae
Han, the all time gold

01:23:22.111 --> 01:23:25.218
medal winner and heart and
soul of the Korean team.

01:23:25.434 --> 01:23:27.153
If you had any doubt
about why he's the most

01:23:27.151 --> 01:23:30.078
feared fighter in the sport
today, just take a look.

01:23:45.617 --> 01:23:46.705
We're just about ready.

01:23:46.703 --> 01:23:49.381
America's hopes rest on Tommy Lee.

01:24:04.977 --> 01:24:06.626
Dae Han opens up quickly with a right to

01:24:06.628 --> 01:24:08.207
Tommy Lee's head.

01:24:23.760 --> 01:24:26.988
That is three unanswered
points by Dae Han.

01:24:27.010 --> 01:24:29.039
This does not look like the same Tommy Lee

01:24:29.045 --> 01:24:31.802
that we saw in the North
American championships.

01:24:36.728 --> 01:24:38.517
Tommy Lee now on the attack, the veteran

01:24:38.507 --> 01:24:40.106
Dae Han countering.

01:24:44.475 --> 01:24:47.022
This spectacular aerial
display is the trademark

01:24:47.021 --> 01:24:49.019
of classical Tae Kwon Do.

01:24:50.740 --> 01:24:52.938
Score, Tommy Lee with
an inside crescent kick.

01:24:52.933 --> 01:24:54.222
- All right!

01:25:00.893 --> 01:25:03.859
- Lee again with a
beautiful spinning heel kick.

01:25:03.866 --> 01:25:05.314
- Tommy, yeah!

01:25:07.478 --> 01:25:09.925
- Folks, this Tommy
Lee is some kind of fighter.

01:25:09.918 --> 01:25:12.205
But the Americans may be
too far behind against

01:25:12.209 --> 01:25:14.436
a master like Dae Han.

01:25:46.400 --> 01:25:47.458
- Yeah!

01:25:47.465 --> 01:25:49.663
Drop it like a toilet seat, Tommy!

01:25:55.915 --> 01:25:58.481
- Illegal hit, illegal hit!

01:25:58.482 --> 01:26:00.201
- Dae Han with
a kick to the groin.

01:26:00.198 --> 01:26:03.334
An illegal move even
in full contact karate.

01:26:08.297 --> 01:26:09.496
And there it is.

01:26:09.490 --> 01:26:12.147
The referee is giving Dae Han a warning.

01:26:12.228 --> 01:26:13.567
Illegal hit.

01:26:24.055 --> 01:26:26.972
- Coach, how many points to win?

01:26:26.975 --> 01:26:29.502
- Six or knockout.

01:26:30.086 --> 01:26:31.654
- Or a knockout.

01:26:31.844 --> 01:26:33.143
If he doesn't knock me out first.

01:26:33.145 --> 01:26:34.494
- You can do it.

01:26:55.489 --> 01:26:57.207
- Korean crowd is coming alive.

01:26:57.205 --> 01:26:59.452
Young support trying to bring Dae Han

01:26:59.452 --> 01:27:01.310
back into this match and crush any hope

01:27:01.306 --> 01:27:03.205
of an American upset.

01:27:04.994 --> 01:27:06.033
- Illegal hit, again!

01:27:06.527 --> 01:27:08.975
- It's another
illegal blow by Dae Han,

01:27:08.968 --> 01:27:10.836
but the referee didn't see it.

01:27:23.994 --> 01:27:25.373
What a move!

01:27:25.378 --> 01:27:27.326
A crushing blow by Tommy Lee to Dae Han.

01:27:27.328 --> 01:27:28.767
Is it possible?

01:27:28.767 --> 01:27:31.014
Can 26 year old Tommy Lee
bring the American team

01:27:31.014 --> 01:27:33.751
back from a seven point deficit?

01:27:33.774 --> 01:27:35.573
Score, Tommy Lee.

01:27:36.300 --> 01:27:37.948
With a minute and a
half left on the clock,

01:27:37.951 --> 01:27:41.098
Tommy Lee has clearly taken
control of this fight.

01:27:41.521 --> 01:27:43.329
With the American team
trailing, the question now

01:27:43.331 --> 01:27:45.859
is there time for Lee
to score enough points

01:27:45.857 --> 01:27:48.195
for an American team victory?

01:28:08.870 --> 01:28:10.698
This could be it.

01:28:10.703 --> 01:28:12.052
This could be it!

01:28:12.046 --> 01:28:14.594
If he doesn't get up,
it's a technical knockout.

01:28:14.593 --> 01:28:17.240
The American team will
win this tournament!

01:29:06.389 --> 01:29:07.897
- No.

01:29:09.106 --> 01:29:11.294
- No, Tommy, no.

01:29:12.653 --> 01:29:15.081
Tommy, no, no!

01:29:15.273 --> 01:29:18.309
Coach, coach, he's gonna kill him!

01:29:18.309 --> 01:29:19.839
- No!

01:29:25.042 --> 01:29:26.550
- Why doesn't Lee finish him?

01:29:26.555 --> 01:29:28.194
A knockout would end it.

01:29:28.196 --> 01:29:29.415
What is going on?

01:29:29.408 --> 01:29:31.556
Dae Han is completely helpless and the

01:29:31.560 --> 01:29:33.758
American will not finish him off.

01:30:36.103 --> 01:30:38.141
- You won that match.

01:30:39.074 --> 01:30:41.531
Don't ever forget that.

01:31:44.423 --> 01:31:45.861
- Just a minute,
ladies and gentlemen,

01:31:45.861 --> 01:31:47.620
there is something going on here.

01:31:47.620 --> 01:31:49.778
Dae Han is making some sort of gesture

01:31:49.783 --> 01:31:51.561
to the American team.

01:32:00.843 --> 01:32:05.408
- To save a life in defeat

01:32:06.778 --> 01:32:11.773
is to earn victory and honor within.

01:32:14.482 --> 01:32:19.477
Your brother too was a great fighter.

01:32:21.004 --> 01:32:25.999
I deeply regret your loss

01:32:27.535 --> 01:32:30.273
and I offer myself

01:32:31.232 --> 01:32:33.890
as your brother.

01:33:27.589 --> 01:33:32.584
- Alexander Grady, Portland, Oregan.

01:33:36.198 --> 01:33:40.534
I know everything about you.

01:34:00.024 --> 01:34:03.410
- Sae Jin Kwon, Seoul, Korea,

01:34:04.244 --> 01:34:07.091
I know all I ever want to know about you.

01:35:04.464 --> 01:35:08.399
We started off heading for the top

01:35:08.800 --> 01:35:12.267
and set our sights on the sun

01:35:13.903 --> 01:35:17.929
There's no more tears,
now we're standing here

01:35:18.101 --> 01:35:22.297
and the morning light has begun.

01:35:23.600 --> 01:35:27.426
They said that you'll expire

01:35:27.628 --> 01:35:31.514
You're wasting your time to try

01:35:33.063 --> 01:35:38.057
But inside a heart of fire
is a force you can't deny

01:35:42.567 --> 01:35:47.561
Something so strong
driving me on, never tire

01:35:52.264 --> 01:35:56.899
Something so strong, born of the sun

01:35:57.271 --> 01:36:02.267
Like a fire burns inside me so strong

01:36:10.314 --> 01:36:14.409
We live in hope, waiting for the day

01:36:14.533 --> 01:36:18.978
When all our dreams can begin

01:36:19.541 --> 01:36:23.507
The time it takes for the rain to fall

01:36:23.793 --> 01:36:28.069
Is the time it takes to give in

01:36:29.355 --> 01:36:33.292
They said that you'll expire

01:36:33.372 --> 01:36:37.208
You're wasting your time to try

01:36:38.220 --> 01:36:43.216
Inside a heart of fire
is a force you can't deny

01:36:48.498 --> 01:36:53.493
Something so strong
driving me on, never tire

01:36:57.864 --> 01:37:02.589
Something so strong, born of the sun

01:37:03.303 --> 01:37:08.298
Like a fire, sea of fire,
burns inside me so strong
